WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
narrator: ephemeral mode — short-lived joins that vanish on logout.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:15.000
narrator: tailscale up with --ephemeral writes no persistent state.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:25.000
narrator: a build-host CI runner is the canonical use case.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:35.000
narrator: the node still gets a 100.64.x.x while it is live.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:45.000
narrator: ping a peer to confirm the ephemeral peer is full-mesh.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:55.000
narrator: a tailscale logout drops the node from the control plane.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:05.000
narrator: the operator sees the node disappear from headscale nodes list.
